04:09.875 --> 04:13.045
And on the Second Day,
God created...

04:13.087 --> 04:15.255
The Hunters.

04:15.297 --> 04:17.174
- Come on, let's go.
- Meyer...

04:17.216 --> 04:18.610
- Another sweep of files.
- Didn't realize we were

04:18.634 --> 04:20.552
running a kindergarten.

04:20.594 --> 04:23.013
There may be something
in Richter's things here,

04:23.055 --> 04:24.223
if we dig.

04:24.264 --> 04:26.225
So let's dive in.

04:26.266 --> 04:27.977
Mr. O, I'm not risking

04:28.018 --> 04:31.271
going to jail 'cause you got
a soft spot for Ruth's grandkid.

04:31.313 --> 04:33.153
Now, you're not paying me enough
for this shit.

04:33.190 --> 04:35.085
Oh, you're the only one
he's paying at all, dearie.

04:35.109 --> 04:36.860
Some of us got responsibilities.

04:36.902 --> 04:39.613
Meyer, Ruthie...
Zikhronah livrakha...

04:39.655 --> 04:41.448
Wanted the boy

04:41.490 --> 04:43.242
- kept from this place.
- That's right.

04:43.283 --> 04:44.923
- He is meant to be here.
- No, he is not.

04:44.952 --> 04:46.832
- Yes, he is.
You're gonna come at me
for my kid?

04:49.665 --> 04:51.166
But she didn't want this.

04:51.208 --> 04:53.794
Trust me. Trust and you'll see.

04:57.131 --> 04:59.299
♪ ♪

05:15.190 --> 05:16.918
- Who's "Karl Holstedder"?
- What did you say?

05:16.942 --> 05:19.653
- Who's "Karl Holstedder"?
- Holstedder.

05:19.695 --> 05:20.988
- Uh...
- Yes.

05:21.030 --> 05:23.407
Gene Martin,
aka Heinz Richter...

05:23.449 --> 05:25.576
-Yes.
-This letter
was among his things

05:25.617 --> 05:27.036
in the toy shop.

05:27.077 --> 05:31.248
Every eighth letter:
"Send instructions #4...

05:31.290 --> 05:33.959
- Right.
- "...to Karl Holstedder.

05:34.001 --> 05:37.546
- 147 Ocean Way..."
- Oh, yeah.

05:37.588 --> 05:39.214
"Port Washington, NY."

05:39.256 --> 05:40.924
- It's a coded message.
- Yes.

05:40.966 --> 05:43.385
Encyclopedia Brown-stein
over here.

05:43.427 --> 05:46.096
You can't change
a creature's nature.

05:46.138 --> 05:47.514
A bear hunts.

05:47.556 --> 05:49.141
A hog shits.

05:49.183 --> 05:51.727
A Nazi plots.

05:51.769 --> 05:54.563
There's no Karl Holstedder
on the list.

05:54.605 --> 05:56.899
So we search the Ark.
Come on.

05:56.940 --> 05:58.650
Let's do it.

05:58.692 --> 06:00.402
We're all gonna fit in here?

06:00.444 --> 06:02.905
Bringing the kid
was a big mistake.

06:02.946 --> 06:05.574
You know what?
I-I'm not a kid. Okay?

06:05.616 --> 06:07.659
I was bar mitzvahed
seven years ago, Sister.

06:07.701 --> 06:10.871
Chanted a little Leviticus,
boogied to Mungo Jerry.

06:10.913 --> 06:12.557
After my haftorah, got
an over-the-pants hand job

06:12.581 --> 06:14.583
from Ruchel Rekenstein.

06:14.625 --> 06:16.394
I know you think
I'm this undescended testicle,

06:16.418 --> 06:17.878
but I'm old enough
to drink, smoke,

06:17.920 --> 06:20.255
enlist in the Army, so...
I'm not a kid.

06:20.297 --> 06:22.966
And unless you want to Greyhound
over to the Indian casino

06:23.008 --> 06:25.761
and recruit
the Navajo Windtalkers,

06:25.803 --> 06:27.429
I think you fucking need me.

06:31.892 --> 06:35.187
One misstep
and I will do things to you

06:35.229 --> 06:37.189
so traumatizing,
you'll wet your knickers

06:37.231 --> 06:40.234
any time you even see Mary
fucking Poppins on the telly.

06:42.069 --> 06:43.612
Are we clear, boy?

06:46.490 --> 06:48.700
You like bar mitzvahs?

06:48.742 --> 06:50.786
Welcome to ours.

06:50.828 --> 06:52.913
You're on, Lonny.

06:52.955 --> 06:56.708
Well, this movie star
needs no introduction,

06:56.750 --> 07:01.171
but let's tell the kid who he's
ménage-à-ocho-ing with, huh?

07:01.213 --> 07:03.006
Take it away, Ruchel.

07:03.048 --> 07:05.384
Shalom, goys and gals.

07:07.302 --> 07:08.846
Former MI6,

07:08.887 --> 07:11.223
now you run logistics
and mission-planning fun.

07:11.265 --> 07:14.726
Sister Harriet,
come light candle number one.

07:14.768 --> 07:16.812
♪ ♪

07:18.647 --> 07:19.731
Hallelujah!

07:19.773 --> 07:22.568
Thank you, thank you.

07:22.609 --> 07:23.819
Amen!

07:23.861 --> 07:25.320
My bedroom's covered
with posters

07:25.362 --> 07:27.322
of this dreamy, hunky Jew.

07:27.364 --> 07:30.492
Lonny Flash,
master of mimicry and disguise,

07:30.534 --> 07:32.703
come light candle number two.

07:32.744 --> 07:34.538
♪ ♪

07:39.585 --> 07:41.086
It's him! It's really him!

07:41.128 --> 07:42.880
Oh, my God, I love your movies!

07:42.921 --> 07:45.007
Like a Jewish Robert Redford,
I'm telling you!

07:45.048 --> 07:46.842
A black power activist,

07:46.884 --> 07:49.678
no detail escapes
Roxy Jones of NYC.

07:49.720 --> 07:52.514
Will this counterfeiter, forger,
and crime scene cleaner

07:52.556 --> 07:54.141
light candle number three?

07:54.183 --> 07:57.311
♪ ♪

07:59.855 --> 08:01.565
Power to the people!

08:01.607 --> 08:03.025
Groovy, baby!

08:05.319 --> 08:08.655
This human weapon is home from
'Nam after three long tours.

08:08.697 --> 08:12.701
Joe Mizushima, forever soldier,
light candle number four.

08:12.743 --> 08:15.120
♪ ♪

08:17.581 --> 08:19.750
God bless America!

08:19.791 --> 08:22.461
Got a nice tochis, that one!

08:22.502 --> 08:24.129
Mindy and Murray,
you've survived

08:24.171 --> 08:25.756
the greatest horror in life.

08:25.797 --> 08:28.258
Will you genius, gadget-making
weapons experts

08:28.300 --> 08:29.676
light candle number five?

08:29.718 --> 08:31.929
♪ ♪

08:40.187 --> 08:41.980
Baruch Hashem!

08:42.022 --> 08:44.691
And finally, my bat mitzvah bash

08:44.733 --> 08:47.402
wouldn't be possible
without this titan of design.

08:47.444 --> 08:49.821
Meyer Offerman,
millionaire bankroller,

08:49.863 --> 08:51.907
master plotter,
and chief vigilante,

08:51.949 --> 08:54.534
come light this sixth candle
of mine.

08:54.576 --> 08:56.578
♪ ♪

09:07.172 --> 09:09.466
Okay, everybody, say cheese!

09:09.508 --> 09:10.634
Cheese!

09:10.676 --> 09:12.594
Marvelous.

09:12.636 --> 09:15.597
Now that we're all mischpocha,

09:15.639 --> 09:18.934
let's go find this
Karl Holstedder motherfucker,

09:18.976 --> 09:20.352
shall we?

09:20.394 --> 09:23.063
Leave no stone unturned.

09:23.105 --> 09:25.482
- No.
- Pore over every file.

09:25.524 --> 09:27.609
Look for anything connected
to a Karl Holstedder

09:27.651 --> 09:29.695
or 147 Ocean Way.

09:29.736 --> 09:31.530
So this is...

09:31.571 --> 09:33.407
The Ark.

09:33.448 --> 09:36.618
This is the house
that Ruth built.

09:36.660 --> 09:39.371
She did this.

09:39.413 --> 09:41.456
Like Noah before her,

09:41.498 --> 09:43.500
Ruth built a vessel

09:43.542 --> 09:48.547
to guard from extinction
today's endangered species:

09:48.588 --> 09:51.216
memory, truth.

09:51.258 --> 09:53.010
How?

09:53.051 --> 09:54.720
How did she do all this?

09:54.761 --> 09:58.557
She unearthed
all the classified files,

09:58.598 --> 10:00.434
records,

10:00.475 --> 10:03.020
interviewed
thousands of survivors.

10:12.404 --> 10:14.823
Wish I knew about all this
while she was still around.

10:14.865 --> 10:18.201
She's still around, kindeleh.

10:18.243 --> 10:21.538
The Ark breathes of her.

10:21.580 --> 10:23.749
It beats of her.

10:23.790 --> 10:26.251
Can't you feel it?

10:26.293 --> 10:28.295
She is here.

10:33.383 --> 10:35.385
♪ ♪

10:48.815 --> 10:50.817
Where do I start?

10:56.031 --> 10:58.992
Sommers!

10:59.034 --> 11:00.869
Sommers, open up!

11:00.911 --> 11:03.246
Hey, lady, it's 5:00
in the fucking morning!

11:03.288 --> 11:05.248
Sir, if you know
what's good for you,

11:05.290 --> 11:06.541
you will go back to watching

11:06.583 --> 11:08.335
your penis pump commercial,
okay?

11:08.377 --> 11:10.337
I'm tired, I'm hungry,
I'm in fucking Florida.

11:10.379 --> 11:12.839
Don't fuck with me
right now, okay? Sommers!

11:12.881 --> 11:14.466
- What the hell are you doing?
- Hey.

11:14.508 --> 11:16.009
You...

11:17.010 --> 11:18.887
I went by Gretel's place.

11:18.929 --> 11:20.347
What, you been there all night?

11:20.389 --> 11:22.182
Uh-huh.

11:22.224 --> 11:24.267
I had a hunch.

11:24.309 --> 11:27.437
So... I scoured again.

11:27.479 --> 11:29.523
And I found this.

11:41.785 --> 11:44.538
- But NASA said
she was a war refugee.
- Mm-hmm.

11:44.579 --> 11:46.456
And yet here she is,

11:46.498 --> 11:48.750
looking as excited
as a white girl

11:48.792 --> 11:52.003
at an Engelbert Humperdinck
concert.

11:52.045 --> 11:55.298
So you think she was a... Nazi?

11:55.340 --> 11:57.426
I think she was a Nazi chemist.

11:57.467 --> 12:00.762
Zyklon B.
Industrial-grade pesticide.

12:00.804 --> 12:03.932
That was the same shit
used to gas her.

12:03.974 --> 12:07.394
Like I said, it felt personal.

12:07.436 --> 12:09.980
I think...

12:10.021 --> 12:12.816
Gretel had something
to do with the gas chambers.

12:12.858 --> 12:14.401
Jesus.

12:14.443 --> 12:16.069
How'd a Nazi get
into the States?

12:16.111 --> 12:18.172
I'm on the first flight
back to New York to find out.

12:18.196 --> 12:20.782
Talk to INS, the Bureau,
see what they can tell me.

12:20.824 --> 12:23.785
Yeah, I'll do some digging
around here. See what comes up.

12:23.827 --> 12:27.080
I'll give you a call
if I find something.

12:27.122 --> 12:29.875
She looked so little,
didn't she?

12:29.916 --> 12:31.501
She didn't look like no monster.

12:31.543 --> 12:34.212
She looked old and little
and ordinary.

12:35.213 --> 12:36.965
Monsters can be little.

12:37.007 --> 12:40.010
Monsters can be old.

12:40.051 --> 12:42.804
Hell, monsters can be us.

12:42.846 --> 12:44.973
This is your captain speaking.
We're at 35,000 feet...

12:45.015 --> 12:48.018
- When are we gonna get there?
- Stop. Stop, put your foot down.

12:48.059 --> 12:51.354
I want to see Tyler Tiger
at Wally World.

12:51.396 --> 12:52.522
- Shh.
- Peanuts?

12:52.564 --> 12:54.608
No, he's allergic.

12:54.649 --> 12:57.736
I'll have.

12:57.777 --> 13:00.697
There you are.

13:00.739 --> 13:02.532
Peanuts?

13:05.368 --> 13:06.870
Is it bad?

13:09.080 --> 13:13.084
His allergy.
Is it... deadly?

13:13.126 --> 13:16.505
It can be, yes.

13:19.925 --> 13:24.179
Scary.
What a way to go.

13:24.221 --> 13:26.932
Well...

13:26.973 --> 13:29.851
there'll be a cure soon.

13:29.893 --> 13:31.520
I won't rest till there is.

13:31.561 --> 13:34.272
Oh, you and me both.

13:36.942 --> 13:39.819
You know...

13:39.861 --> 13:43.365
allergies are
a modern invention.

13:43.406 --> 13:48.245
Like depression
or schizophrenia.

13:49.996 --> 13:53.458
Because once upon a time,
we let nature reign,

13:53.500 --> 13:58.380
and it weeded out the sick
and the weak from our gene pool.

13:58.421 --> 14:01.800
It kept us... pure.

14:04.094 --> 14:09.224
These days, well,
there is a drug for everything.

14:09.266 --> 14:12.477
Yet suddenly the whole
population is now sick,

14:12.519 --> 14:15.772
and the sick have created
so much violence and suffering

14:15.814 --> 14:18.692
that a person has to hop on
a plane and pay a small fortune

14:18.733 --> 14:20.569
to take pictures
with anthropomorphic animals

14:20.610 --> 14:22.612
just to keep himself sane.

14:24.072 --> 14:25.824
All because we tell
the nice stewardess

14:25.865 --> 14:30.495
a little boy shouldn't have
any Miss Petunia's Peanuts.

14:30.537 --> 14:32.539
Or perhaps he should.

14:32.581 --> 14:35.834
Because he is the poison,

14:35.875 --> 14:40.130
and this is the cure.

14:41.506 --> 14:43.925
So... peanut?

14:50.682 --> 14:52.350
Tonight on First with Frist,

14:52.392 --> 14:55.812
Biff Simpson on the tragic
massacre of his family.

14:55.854 --> 15:00.025
It'll be the little things
I miss most.

15:00.066 --> 15:03.653
Eating Little Caesars pizza...

15:03.695 --> 15:06.156
watching Six Million Dollar Man,

15:06.197 --> 15:08.199
cuddled on the couch.

15:08.241 --> 15:12.412
Just telling 'em "I love you."

15:16.041 --> 15:18.376
I wish I could have done more.

15:20.587 --> 15:24.549
I wish it'd... it'd been me.

15:27.260 --> 15:29.679
But my Lottie always said...

15:32.349 --> 15:36.561
love means never having
to say you're sorry.

15:46.821 --> 15:48.406
This has been
a special presentation

15:48.448 --> 15:50.116
of First with Frist.

15:50.158 --> 15:52.827
And now back
to your regular programming,

15:52.869 --> 15:55.163
Me and the Chimp.

16:02.003 --> 16:04.297
You don't remember us, do you?

16:04.339 --> 16:06.883
I don't think so.

16:06.925 --> 16:09.511
My mother always said, "Murray,
you have a forgettable face."

16:09.552 --> 16:11.680
Ages five to eight,
she reintroduced herself

16:11.721 --> 16:13.098
every time she saw me.

16:13.139 --> 16:15.058
True story.

16:15.100 --> 16:17.644
Oh, well, you-you were

16:17.686 --> 16:22.315
just a yingeleh...
F-five or six years old.

16:22.357 --> 16:27.278
Your safta took you to meet us
at Art's Deli.

16:27.320 --> 16:29.322
- Yeah, yeah. Mm-hmm.
- Remember that, Murray?

16:29.364 --> 16:33.243
Cute as a kugel you were.

16:33.284 --> 16:36.788
You looked just like him.

16:36.830 --> 16:39.541
Hey, got something.

16:39.582 --> 16:42.001
An SS roll from Buchenwald.

16:42.043 --> 16:45.296
Names a Nazi engineer,
Karl Holstedder.

16:45.338 --> 16:48.007
Buchenwald. Engineer.
10-4, Eleanor.

16:49.467 --> 16:51.261
Yeah.

16:53.179 --> 16:55.849
Karl Holstedder,

16:55.890 --> 17:00.019
the Pied Piper of Buchenwald.

17:00.061 --> 17:02.647
He was the emcee
of the Buchenwald camp.

17:02.689 --> 17:05.024
A brilliant radio engineer,

17:05.066 --> 17:07.694
he ran the camp's
control center.

17:07.736 --> 17:10.572
But on Saturday, Shabbos,

17:10.613 --> 17:13.491
he held his horror show,
The Star of Buchenwald.

17:13.533 --> 17:15.410
Good Evening, Buchenwald!

17:15.452 --> 17:16.786
Your master of ceremonies,

17:16.828 --> 17:19.164
Hauptsturmfuhrer Holstedder
here.

17:19.205 --> 17:21.332
Back for another episode of

17:21.374 --> 17:24.544
THE STAR OF BUCHENWALD!

17:35.972 --> 17:38.725
It was a singing competition.

17:38.767 --> 17:41.561
A sadistic Gong Show.

17:41.603 --> 17:46.524
Every Shabbos,
Holstedder rounded up ten men

17:46.566 --> 17:51.112
and made them sing
for their lives.

17:57.827 --> 17:59.829
If you sang out of tune...

17:59.871 --> 18:01.998
It's a D-flat,

18:02.040 --> 18:04.042
Number 218763.

18:19.808 --> 18:21.351
If you forgot the words...

18:21.392 --> 18:23.937
Come on, 217742:

18:25.980 --> 18:30.652
"In the Graceland
of our Fathers."

18:39.869 --> 18:42.789
Someone is
a quarter step ahead...

18:46.334 --> 18:49.087
Until there was only one left.

18:57.428 --> 19:02.016
Well, Mr. Holstedder...

19:02.058 --> 19:04.811
come on down.

19:11.192 --> 19:14.279
So, how do you like The Hunters?

19:14.320 --> 19:16.406
They scare the shit out of me.

19:18.408 --> 19:20.827
Yes!

19:20.869 --> 19:24.789
How'd you recruit 'em, anyway,
Professor X?

19:27.917 --> 19:30.295
No.

19:32.672 --> 19:34.716
Well...

19:36.134 --> 19:38.928
I went to a matchmaker.

19:38.970 --> 19:42.181
-♪ Matchmaker, matchmaker,
make me a match... ♪
-But that's not all she is.

19:46.144 --> 19:48.938
♪ Night after night,
in the dark I'm alone... ♪

19:48.980 --> 19:50.732
Yes, thank you.

19:50.773 --> 19:53.568
♪ Of my own. ♪

19:53.610 --> 19:56.237
Oh, my God.

19:56.279 --> 19:59.324
- Shalom, my dear love.
- I can't believe this.

19:59.365 --> 20:02.035
- Oh, I can't either.
- Mwah.

20:02.076 --> 20:05.121
- My darling.
- Come sit, Meyerleh, sit.

20:05.163 --> 20:07.582
Eh, what a neighborhood.

20:07.624 --> 20:09.250
I know. Very fancy.

20:09.292 --> 20:14.213
- It is fancy.
I'm so glad I dressed.

20:14.255 --> 20:16.049
30 years in our new shtetl
of Manhattan,

20:16.090 --> 20:20.219
you don't break fast with me,
you don't venture to my sukkah.

20:20.261 --> 20:23.806
What did a little old matchmaker
do to deserve such kavod?

20:23.848 --> 20:25.934
Well, I wasn't looking
to be matched, Hilda.

20:25.975 --> 20:28.227
So, if that's all right
with you...

20:28.269 --> 20:31.147
It's 40 years pining
only for Ruth.

20:31.189 --> 20:33.358
This is the oldest
"Will They or Won't They"

20:33.399 --> 20:35.568
in the world,
since-since Jacob and Rachel.

20:35.610 --> 20:36.986
Oh, God.

20:37.028 --> 20:41.449
You have a lot of security
for a little old matchmaker, no?

20:41.491 --> 20:45.161
Well, you know, can you think
of a creature more dangerous

20:45.203 --> 20:47.372
than a Jewish mother
with an unwed daughter?

20:49.874 --> 20:53.002
Matchmaker in the daylight.

20:53.044 --> 20:55.922
But don't sell yourself short,
because you've commodified

20:55.964 --> 20:58.800
the occupation of yenta.

20:58.841 --> 21:02.261
You weaponized the Rolodex.

21:02.303 --> 21:05.264
You are the Jewish world's
fixer, no?

